}\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3985:            coverage=None,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3986:            reason=\"job_failed\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4010:    \"\"\"Append issue context and concrete chunk limits for oversized dynamic-access runs.\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4015:    (§WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report).\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4049:            pipeline_argv.append(\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\")\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4164:            driver_name=\"improve_library_coverage\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4165:            script_name=\"improve_library_coverage.py\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4166:            runner_name=\"run_improve_library_coverage_workflow\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4167:            runner=run_improve_library_coverage_workflow,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4174:            log_stage_name=\"improve-coverage-workflow\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4176:                f\"Invoking improve_library_coverage workflow for issue #{issue_number}: \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4179:            failure_name=\"improve_library_coverage\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4834:    (§WF-dynamic-access-exhaust-report).\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5090:    (§WF-chunked-dynamic-access-pr-linking, §GIT-issue-linking).\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5233:        script_name = \"git_scripts/make_pr_improve_coverage.py\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5234:        runner_name = \"run_make_pr_improve_coverage\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5235:        runner = run_make_pr_improve_coverage\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5307:        title, body, _matched = build_improve_coverage_pull_request_preview(\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:6739:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:6742:            \"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:6743:            \"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\nforge/prompt_templates/persistent/default_agent_rules.md:4:- Keep generated tests meaningful and avoid replacing real coverage with trivial assertions.\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:27:    collect_version_coverage_metrics,\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:194:    previous_coverage, _ = collect_version_coverage_metrics(repo_path, group, artifact, old_version)\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:195:    new_coverage, _ = collect_version_coverage_metrics(repo_path, group, artifact, new_version)\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:211:        f\"- Library coverage (previous): {previous_coverage:.2f}%\\n\"\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_ni_run_fix.py:212:        f\"- Library coverage (new): {new_coverage:.2f}%\"\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:1:# WF-dynamic-access-workflow: Dynamic-access workflow specification\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:3:The dynamic-access workflow is part of the Forge workflow system\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:8:The dynamic-access workflow family generates or improves JUnit/Kotlin/Scala\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:9:tests for a target library so that **dynamic-access call sites** reported by\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:10:the reachability repo's coverage tool are exercised at runtime. Coverage of\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:14:class-by-class refinement (§GOAL-maximize-library-coverage).\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:16:### WF-dynamic-access-strategy-family: Dynamic-access strategy family\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:18:Forge currently has three registered dynamic-access workflow engines:\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:22:| `dynamic_access_iterative` | Per-class dynamic-access generation or refinement. It selects one uncovered class at a time, prompts with that class's remaining call sites, verifies coverage deltas, and commits resolved or partially resolved class progress (§WF-dynamic-access-iterative-strategy). | `dynamic_access_*`, `library_update_pi_gpt-5.5` |\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:23:| `optimistic_dynamic_access` | Bulk dynamic-access generation or refinement. It gives the agent the full dynamic-access report and asks for a broad coverage pass, then verifies tests, regenerates the report, commits the attempt, and runs the native-test verification gate (§WF-dynamic-access-bulk-strategy). | `dynamic_access_bulk_*`, `dynamic_access_graphify_bulk_*`, `library_update_dynamic_access_bulk_pi_gpt-5.5` |\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:24:| `increase_dynamic_access_coverage` | Composite coverage workflow. It optionally runs a configured primary workflow first, then runs the iterative dynamic-access phase against any remaining uncovered call sites (§WF-dynamic-access-composite-strategy). | `optimistic_dynamic_access_iterative_*`, `library_update_optimistic_pi_gpt-5.5`, Java-fix composite strategies |\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:32:#### WF-dynamic-access-iterative-strategy: Iterative dynamic-access strategy\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:35:class-scoped, reviewable progress through a dynamic-access report. It generates\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:36:the initial dynamic-access report, falls back to the basic iterative workflow\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:39:repair attempts, coverage-delta checks, per-class checkpointing, and native-test\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:40:verification after each configured batch of coverage-gain commits.\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:44:verification gates. Otherwise it returns success only when the dynamic-access\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:47:#### WF-dynamic-access-bulk-strategy: Bulk dynamic-access strategy\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:50:give the agent the full dynamic-access report and ask for a broad pass rather\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:52:attempt, for library-update coverage improvement, and for Graphify-assisted\nforge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:56:The bulk engine ref